            . On the 17th of November,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183112010093"></xptr>about half-past two o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18311201-192-crimeloc1026">Whitechapel</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-192-crimeloc1026" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-192-crimeloc1026" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-192-off1024 t18311201-192-crimeloc1026"></join>; I felt a tug at my pocket, turned round, and saw the prisoner - I took him with my handkerchief in his hand; this is it.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM HOMER. I am a Police-officer. I was opposite the hospital: the prosecutor gave the prisoner to me and this handkerchief.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Two men were quarrelling; some boys who stood by me dropped this handkerchief - the gentleman seized me; I showed him the boy who took it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character, and a witness engaged to employ him.</p>
               <p>
